Metadata: Flotsam, Jetsam and Wrack on Oregon Beaches
Oregon State University Extension Marine Advisory Program

"Flotsam," "jetsam," and "wrack" are words with romance about them, meaning more or less the same thing-items washed onto the ocean beach from the open sea. Discussed are: plastic discs, oil, drift bottles, brain coral, Velella velella (jellyfishes), skate egg cases, rock scallop, cellophane tube worms, bull kelp and sea palm, foam, and lingcod eggs.
